Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithmic complexity and information theory, which are closely related to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of computational devices such as Turing Machines and Cellular Automata suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The comparison of frequency distributions and the analysis of noise in the data could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of NKS (New Kind of Science) and the exploration of patterns in abstract systems could be related to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the study of convergence in the infinite limit case could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
